10175603		20200529	JTB00662NAS2	20200506		Service Bulletin/Repair Instructions	JAGUAR	F-PACE	2019	POWER TRAIN:AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION:COOLING UNIT AND LINES			A transmission fluid leak may be seen coming from below the vehicle. There may also be a lack of acceleration and/or a 'juddering' from the vehicle while driving. A transmission warning message may also be displayed on the Instrument Panel Cluster (IPC). Upon further diagnosis, the fluid may be found leaking from the transmission fluid cooler pipe(s).  
10175603		20200529	JTB00662NAS2	20200506		Service Bulletin/Repair Instructions	JAGUAR	F-PACE	2017	POWER TRAIN:AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION:COOLING UNIT AND LINES			A transmission fluid leak may be seen coming from below the vehicle. There may also be a lack of acceleration and/or a 'juddering' from the vehicle while driving. A transmission warning message may also be displayed on the Instrument Panel Cluster (IPC). Upon further diagnosis, the fluid may be found leaking from the transmission fluid cooler pipe(s).

10204091		20211207	H382NAS1	20211118		Service Bulletin/Repair Instructions	JAGUAR	XF	2021	ELECTRICAL SYSTEM			A potential issue has been identified on specific vehicles where, in locations where the vehicle has poor or no network connection, vehicles may experience intermittent resetting of the navigation system, following a recent  Map Over The Air (MOTA) update. The navigation screen displayed on the Touchscreen will revert to the PIVI home screen and the navigation screen displayed in the instrument cluster panel will revert to displaying the manufacturer's logo. The system will self-recover and navigation will resume, however this fault may re-occur if the vehicle maintains poor or no network connection. No other vehicle features or systems are affected.

10204162		20211207	IC TP 21B	20211116		Service Bulletin/Repair Instructions	JAGUAR	XJ	2018	EQUIPMENT:ELECTRICAL:INFOTAINMENT			4X4I SCREEN  The screen will show the correct pitch and roll angle of the vehicle  APPLE CARPLAY  Turn by turn voice guidance will now work in Apple CarPlay Maps  INSTRUMENT PANEL CLUSTER CONTROL MODULE B (IPCB)  When playing FM radio source the IPCB will no longer show a Gray background  COMPASS VIEW  The north indicator "N" in compass view will be updated when there is a theme change  HOTSPOT CONNECTIVITY  Improved stability of Hotspot functionality  DVD  Improved stability of DVD functionality  ELECTRIC VEHICLE (EV) CHARGING  Charging port will flash green instead of blue when charging  MEDIA PLAYER  Album art is now available in media library  STEERING WHEEL CONTROLS  Improved stability of Steering wheel control functionality after using rear media feature   REAR SEAT ENTERTAINMENT (RSE)  Video can now be played on both rear screens at the same time  In the rear right screen, the text for passenger and driver seats are no longer swapped in German  SELF-LEARNING CAR  Improved stability of self learning car mode  SETTINGS  In the Chattanooga region in USA near the Eastern/Central time zone border the infotainment time is now no longer 1 hour behind in Auto mode  Telematic Control Unit Module (TCU) installation popup will no longer display message in English while the language is set to Chinese  SYSTEM   Improved stability on start up  TIMED CLIMATE  Timed climate icon will no longer appear on Interactive Display Module 'A' (IDMA) while vehicle is in motion

10206243		20220108	H367NAS2	20211215		Service Bulletin/Repair Instructions	JAGUAR	E-PACE	2021	LANE DEPARTURE: LANE KEEP: STEERING ASSIST			Vehicles may experience a loss of steering assistance, with a 'Steering Assistance Reduced' message, along with other related messages, displayed on the instrument panel cluster. The steering assistance will drop to 50% for 10seconds and then 0% but after the ignition is cycled the steering assistance and related features will return to normal.
